  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Male &amp; female aged ≥ 40 to ≤ 65 years suffering from primary idiopathic osteoarthritis
             of the knee diagnosed at least 3 months prior to screening.

          2. BMI ≥ 18 and ≤ 29.9 kg/m2.

          3. Fasting blood sugar ≤ 126 mg/dl

          4. Index knee joint pain rated ≥ 60 on a 100-point Pain-Visual Analogue Scale (VAS).

          5. Systolic blood pressure &lt; 140 mmHg and diastolic blood pressure &lt; 90 mmHg

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. History of osteoarthritis for more than 3 years.

          2. Current smokers or chronic alcoholics

          3. Participants with deformity of the knee joint
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
